All CSS rules are made of two components:

SELECTOR        DECLARATION
#page-header    { font-size: 10px; }

Selector can target
    - tag names
    - ID
    - classes
    - other

#header p { declaration }       // #header -> ID,  p -> tag
.comment div { declaration }    // .comment -> class, div -> tag
li { declaration }              // li -> tag


Declaration contain properties and values
#selector { font-size : 10px; }
#selector {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: red;
}


Inline / Embedded / External Style Sheet

Inline
    <body>
        <p style="font-size: 10px"> Hello world</p>
        <p style="font-size: 10px"> Hello world2</p>
        <p style="font-size: 10px"> Hello world3</p>

Embedded
    <head> 
        ..
        <style>
        p { font-size: 10px };
        </style>
        ...
    </head>

External Style Sheet
    <head>
        ...
        <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/sytle.cxx">
        ...
    </head>
